&lt;h3&gt;Month of Elul&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;General Notes&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Each day, Psalm 27 is traditionally recited at the end of the Shacharit and Ma&#039;ariv services. One verse of Psalm 27, Achat Sha&#039;alti, is included in Mishkan T&#039;filah (MT 662). We continue reciting Achat Sha&#039;alti through Hoshanah Rabah or Sh&#039;mini Atzeret/Simchat Torah.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;On weekdays, the shofar is sounded during the shacharit service after the recitation of Psalm 27. No blessing is recited. We sound T&#039;kiah, followed by Sh&#039;varim, T&#039;ruah, and another T&#039;kiah. The shofar is not traditionally sounded on Shabbat or on the morning of Erev Rosh Hashanah.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There is a custom to increase the giving of Tzedakah during this month (JL 117).&lt;/p&gt;
